1ï¸âƒ£ SVM lÃ  gÃ¬?

ğŸ‘‰ SVM tÃ¬m Ä‘Æ°á»ng (hoáº·c máº·t pháº³ng) phÃ¢n chia:

Xa cÃ¡c Ä‘iá»ƒm dá»¯ liá»‡u nháº¥t

Ãt bá»‹ nhiá»…u

ğŸ“Œ Ráº¥t máº¡nh vá»›i dá»¯ liá»‡u nhá»â€“vá»«a

2ï¸âƒ£ Chuáº©n hÃ³a dá»¯ liá»‡u (Báº®T BUá»˜C)
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

X = df[["math", "english"]]
y = df["passed"]

scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_scaled, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42
)

3ï¸âƒ£ Train SVM (Linear)
from sklearn.svm import SVC

model = SVC(kernel="linear")
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

4ï¸âƒ£ Dá»± Ä‘oÃ¡n & Ä‘Ã¡nh giÃ¡
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

5ï¸âƒ£ Dá»± Ä‘oÃ¡n há»c sinh má»›i
new_student = scaler.transform([[6, 8]])
print(model.predict(new_student))

6ï¸âƒ£ Kernel phi tuyáº¿n (RBF â€“ ráº¥t máº¡nh)
model = SVC(kernel="rbf", C=1, gamma="scale")
model.fit(X_train, y_train)
